name: Northern Harrier, Marsh hawk
overview: Northern Harriers fly low over the ground when hunting. And will eat on the ground. Males like to perform flying barrel rolls to court females. It is a predator of the California black rail. Classified as of least concern.
habitat: Northern Harriers breed in wide open habitats such as grasslands and marshes. Their nests are concealed in the ground in grasses or wetland vegetation.
